ch that is holding it that way.";i:10;s:68:"Any pull on the rope does nothing since it is already pulled to max.";i:11;s:47:"I do see some plastic white thingy at the back.";i:12;s:27:"A Faulty Emergency Release.";i:13;s:94:"If your emergency release is faulty it might mean that your garage door is difficult to budge.";i:14;s:81:"This is a particularly annoying issue for automatic garage doors that are broken.";i:15;s:78:"In these cases the emergency release is relied upon to open the door manually.";i:16;s:75:"If this is also faulty your garage door will be stuck in the shut position.";i:17;s:163:"What is probably happening is first of all your garage door opener has too much down pressure or force on the door arm that your emergency release is connected to.";i:18;s:126:"Then your pulling the rope but the little pin is hanging on the tab just a little bit like just on the edge before it lets go.";i:19;s:251:"If the garage door is the only entrance then you can probably save yourself a lot of heartache by ringing us straight away and requesting an emergency call-out because we not only have the expertise but also the special tools needed to open that door.";i:20;s:62:"The manual release helps you to manage an emergency situation.";i:21;s:51:"It also helps to keep things in your garage secure.";i:22;s:90:"If the manual release is damaged or broken you may not be able to respond in an emergency.";i:23;s:120:"Having an experienced garage door technician repair the manual release and check the garage door springs ensures safety.";i:24;s:121:"While the cord itself is just a rope it is an important part of how the garage door functions when attached to an opener.";i:25;s:172:"By passing UL 325 standards the opener still needs an emergency release in case the door itself is stuck or someone gets caught underneath the garage door as it is closing.";i:26;s:142:"Garage Door Openers have an emergency release latch mechanism that allows you to operate the garage door manually in the event you lose power.";i:27;s:70:"The carriage is the part of the opener to which the door arm connects.";i:28;s:69:"The carriage locks around the opener trolley during normal operation.";i:29;s:57:"Once the power comes back on it is necessary to reengage.";i:30;s:110:"Failing or broken garage springs will make your door very difficult and sometimes impossible to open manually.";i:31;s:93:"It will also put added stress on your electric garage door opener causing it to fail as well.";i:32;s:59:"Garage door springs have an expected number of life cycles.";i:33;s:76:"Life cycles are the number of times you can open and close your garage door.";i:34;s:40:"If door is closed open door all the way.";i:35;s:95:"Get a safe ladder With your remote move the belt so that the metal coupler is all the way back.";i:36;s:88:"Then manually move the door so that the realease mechanism is centered on metal coupler.";i:37;s:49:"Now pull on the cord and it will snap into place.";i:38;s:59:"Mine is a genie but if its a belt it should work similarly.";i:39;s:140:"Nonetheless manually moving your garage door will require you to pull the red emergency cord that you can see hanging from your garage door.";i:40;s:77:"Now do you know how to release and reset the emergency cord of a garage door.";i:41;s:123:"We Direct Service Overhead Garage Door Company wants to be sure that you do the releasing of your emergency cord correctly.";i:42;s:164:"If there are any faulty or broken springs the garage door can crash down rapidly potentially harming anything in its path and most certainly damage the door itself.";i:43;s:122:"If your door is stuck in the open position we recommend giving us a quick call so we can help remedy the situation safely.";i:44;s:50:"Step 2 Locate and Pull the Emergency Release Cord.";i:45;s:59:"The emergency release cord is the red rope that hangs from.";i:46;s:172:"The emergency cord will release the garage door from the garage door opener in the event of a power failure or other situation during which the automatic door cant be used.";i:47;s:79:"Its critical never to disconnect the garage door if its in the raised position.";i:48;s:84:"If the spring is broken disconnecting a garage door which is in the raised position.";i:49;s:72:"Pull the emergency release cord to allow you to manually open your door.";i:50;s:97:"This usually has a red plastic handle and hangs in the center of the door assembly near the door.";i:51;s:86:"Feed the other end of the cord through the emergency release lever on the door opener.";i:52;s:66:"Pull the end through until the handle is six feet above the floor.";i:53;s:34:"Tie an overhand knot to secure it.";}}